                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc>
                      Inside front cover: Alphabet, in a poor hand‎
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc type="ScribalNoteCompleting">
                      <locus target="#‎162r"/>, col. 2: Scribal note, <foreign xml:lang="gez">‎ተፈጸመ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዳዊት፡ በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ በወርኃ፡ ፆም፡ በብዙኅ፡ ምንዳቤ፡ በ፳፩ ‎‎፡ ሌሊት፡ በ፲ወ፬፡ መዓልት።‎</foreign> “This Psalter was finished during the year ‎of Mark, the Evangelist, in the fasting season with much suffering, ‎on the twenty-first night, fourteenth day‎"
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#‎162v"/>, col. 2: list of the feast days of the apostles and martyrs‎
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      ‎Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters‎
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      ‎Numbered quires: quires 4, 7, 9–13 and 15–16‎
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                        <desc>
                          ‎words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#23r #‎‎60r #75v #83v"/>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (f<locus target="#‎‎71v #76v"/>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#121r"/>);
                          text has been ‎removed (e.g., <locus target="#14r #16v #34r #102v"/>)‎
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                        <desc>
                          ‎The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. ‎Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an ‎
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate ‎script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the
                          scribe ‎completes the line of text below or above the end of the line ‎‎(throughout). The scribe generally will complete above the line ‎when
                          dealing with the bottom margin (e.g., <locus target="#34v #38r #103r"/>)‎
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
